Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Development Engineer position with Labcorp. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, RESTful API design, and microservices architecture, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the full-stack development expertise and technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and implemented RESTful API endpoints across 1,000+ platform endpoints with Spring Boot-style validation patterns, enabling safe tool calls and automated customer actions in production systems — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across a distributed microservices surface. I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph with containerized deployment, enabling scalable tool execution across complex workflows, and implemented an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing and structured logs to support and troubleshoot production systems, reducing latency by 60% and API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I developed a full-stack Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with responsive design and seamless front-end and back-end integration. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO through RESTful API endpoints, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions, Lambda, and API Gateway to handle long-running data import jobs in microservices architecture, using Jira and Git for agile project planning. Together, these roles have prepared me to develop high-quality, responsive, and scalable web applications, design and implement RESTful API endpoints, and collaborate effectively within an agile development team using Jira, Confluence, and Git.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, technical communication, and collaborative problem-solving — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using PyTorch and CUDA on Pace University's HPC cluster, implementing LORA for model training and fine-tuning. I utilized vLLM for model inference with Hugging Face deployment, implementing RESTful API endpoints for secure model serving, and led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents for 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the code review participation, documentation practices, and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Labcorp's mission-driven engineering team.

I have always been passionate about improving health and improving lives through scientific excellence and innovation, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Labcorp's mission as a global leader in diagnostic testing and drug development solutions. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

